{
  "provenance": {
    "vendored_source": "https://github.com/eyereasoner/eye (reasoning/socrates, reasoning/path, reasoning/dog, reasoning/snaf, reasoning/deep-taxonomy, reasoning/nixon-diamond, reasoning/backward, reasoning/good-cobbler, reasoning/peano, reasoning/skos, reasoning/filter, reasoning/basic-monadic, reasoning/edt)",
    "vendored_description": "The `vendored` suite reproduces EYE reasoner community test cases, lightly adapted where noted in each .n3 file's header comment. All 13 cases (socrates, path, dog, snaf, deep-taxonomy [truncated from a 10000-level chain to 3 levels], nixon-diamond, backward, good-cobbler, peano, skos, filter, basic-monadic [truncated to a 10-node cycle], edt [truncated to a 3-level chain, same feature as deep-taxonomy]) run against this engine's supported subset and are 'active' -- 0 ignored. Everything in `syntax` and hand-authored `builtins` cases is authored for this crate directly.",
    "last_synced": "2026-07-05"
  },
  "runner_semantics": "For every active case, the runner loads `input` via TripleStore::from, calls materialize(), decodes every inferred triple to its 'S P O.' string form, and asserts every triple listed in `expected` is present among them (a subset/entailment check, not exact equality -- both because forward-chaining fixpoints often derive more than any one hand-picked expectation, and because two of the vendored EYE cases were themselves only checked by EYE against a narrow, non-generic query).",
